Package com.milk.util

Interface Summary
Comparator This interface is for objects which know how to compare objects for equality and generate relevant hashcodes to make that determination quicker.
ObjectPredicate An ObjectPredicate merely knows how to answer a true/false question about individual objects.
Orderable This interface is for objects which may be ordered with respect to each other.
Orderer This interface is for objects which know how to impose an order on other objects.
Table A Table is a mapping from keys to values.
TableElement A TableElement holds a key and a value, and is generally used to indicate a mapping from the key to the value in a table of some sort.
 

Class Summary
BaseEvent This is the milk-standard extension to EventObject.
EqComparator This is a comparator which uses == to perform comparisons and System.identityHashCode() as the compare-hash.
EqualsComparator This is a comparator which uses Object.equals() to perform comparisons and Object.hashCode() as the compare-hash.
FalsePredicate This is an ObjectPredicate which answers false to all test()s.
FlatTable This is an implementation of a Table as a flat array.
ListenerList This is a handy class for holding a list of zero or more EventListeners.
PriorityQueue PriorityQueue is just an implementation of the classic priority queue data structure.
StandardOrderer This class implements the "standard" Orderer class, which merely assumes that its first compare() argument is an Orderable and asks it to order itself with respect to the second argument.
StdTableElement This is the standard TableElement implementation which immutably holds a given key and value.
TruePredicate This is an ObjectPredicate which answers true to all test()s.
 

Exception Summary
BadArgumentException This exception is thrown when an argument is inappropriate for a call of some sort.
BadKeyException This exception is thrown when a key is inappropriate in a particular context.
BadValueException This exception is thrown when a value is inappropriate in a particular context.
BugInClientException This is an exception to throw when a program detects unexpected behavior but that behavior is due to code not directly associated with the system that is doing the throwing.
BugInSubclassException This is an exception to throw when a class detects unexpected behavior by a subclass which extends it.
ImmutableException This exception is thrown when attempts are made to set a value to something that is immutable.
RuntimeSubException This is an exception to throw when a program needs to throw a RuntimeException which may embed another exception.
ShouldntHappenException This is an exception to throw when a program detects unexpected behavior.
UnorderedException This is the exception thrown by Orderable.compare() and Orderer.compare() when they are handed handed objects which are unordered.
